-- Section 2: Connection 1-Forms (Gauge Potential)
-- ============================================================

/-- A connection on a principal G-bundle is a Lie algebra-valued 1-form ŌČ
    on the total space P satisfying:
    1. Vertical condition: ŌČ(X) = X for vertical vectors X (generated by G-action)
    2. Equivariance: R_g* ŌČ = Ad(g‚ĀĽ¬? ¬∑ ŌČ

    Locally, ŌČ = g‚ĀĽ¬Ļdg + g‚ĀĽ¬ĻAg where A is the gauge potential (connection 1-form on M). -/
structure Connection {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] (P : PrincipalBundle M G) where
  /-- Lie algebra-valued 1-form on the total space. -/
  omega : P.totalSpace ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?‚Ą?  /-- Vertical condition: ŌČ generates the Lie algebra of the fiber. -/
  vertical : ‚ąÄ (p : P.totalSpace) (X : G), omega p X = X
  /-- Equivariance under right action. -/
  equivariance : ‚ąÄ (p : P.totalSpace) (g : G), omega (P.rightAction p g) = Ad g‚ĀĽ¬?(omega p)

/-- The gauge potential (local connection 1-form) on the base manifold M.

    In a local trivialization, A_őĪ = s_őĪ* ŌČ where s_őĪ is a local section.
    Under gauge transformation g_{őĪő≤}: A_ő≤ = g_{őĪő≤}‚ĀĽ¬?A_őĪ g_{őĪő≤} + g_{őĪő≤}‚ĀĽ¬?dg_{őĪő≤}. -/
structure GaugePotential {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] (P : PrincipalBundle M G) where
  /-- Local 1-form A_őĪ on open sets U_őĪ ‚ä?M. -/
  potential : M ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?‚Ą?  /-- Gauge transformation law. -/
  gaugeTransform : ‚ąÄ (x : M) (g : G), potential x = Ad g‚ĀĽ¬?(potential x) + g‚ĀĽ¬?* (deriv g x)

/-- Parallel transport: horizontal lift of a curve ő≥: [t‚āÄ,t‚āĀ] ‚Ü?M.

    A curve ő≥ŐÉ in P is horizontal if ŌČ(ő≥ŐÉ'(t)) = 0 for all t.
    The parallel transport map P_ő≥: ŌÄ‚ĀĽ¬?ő≥(t‚āÄ)) ‚Ü?ŌÄ‚ĀĽ¬?ő≥(t‚ā?) is defined by
    following the horizontal lift.

    POSTULATED: requires ODE theory on smooth manifolds, which is not yet
    complete in Mathlib. The existence/uniqueness of horizontal lifts depends on:
    (1) ODE existence on manifolds, (2) smooth dependence on initial conditions,
    (3) Frobenius theorem for horizontal distributions. Replaceable once
    Mathlib develops these foundations (estimated 2026‚Ä?028). -/
postulate ParallelTransport {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (conn : Connection P)
    (ő≥ : ‚Ą?‚Ü?M) (t‚āÄ t‚ā?: ‚Ą? : Fiber P (ő≥ t‚āÄ) ‚Ü?Fiber P (ő≥ t‚ā?
  -- Parallel transport requires solving ODEs on manifolds: given a curve
  -- ő≥: [t‚āÄ,t‚āĀ] ‚Ü?M and a point p ‚ą?ŌÄ‚ĀĽ¬?ő≥(t‚āÄ)), find the unique horizontal
  -- lift ő≥ŐÉ with ő≥ŐÉ(t‚āÄ) = p and ŌČ(ő≥ŐÉ'(t)) = 0 for all t.
  --
  -- Why not formalizable in Lean today:
  -- 1. Manifold ODE theory is not yet complete in Mathlib. The existence
  --    and uniqueness theorem for ODEs on manifolds (via exponential maps,
  --    parallel transport, or connection geodesics) requires:
  --    - Existence of solutions to ODEs on smooth manifolds
  --    - Smooth dependence on initial conditions
  --    - Lifting of curves to principal bundles
  -- 2. Mathlib has ODE theory on ‚ĄĚ‚ĀŅ (via Mathlib.Dynamics.ODE) but not
  --    the generalization to arbitrary smooth manifolds with connections.
  -- 3. The horizontal lift equation ŌČ(ő≥ŐÉ') = 0 is a first-order ODE on the
  --    total space P, requiring the Frobenius theorem for integrability of
  --    horizontal distributions.
  --
  -- Postulated as a gauge theory axiom. Will be replaceable once Mathlib
  -- develops manifold ODE theory (estimated: 2026‚Ä?028).

postulate ParallelTransport_horizontal_lift : ‚ąÄ {M G} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G]
  [TopologicalSpace G] [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (conn : Connection P)
  (ő≥ : ‚Ą?‚Ü?M) (t‚āÄ t‚ā?: ‚Ą?,
  -- Horizontal lift of ő≥ exists uniquely given initial point in fiber
  ‚ą? (ő≥ŐÉ : ‚Ą?‚Ü?P.totalSpace), P.proj ‚ą?ő≥ŐÉ = ő≥ ‚ą?conn.omega (ő≥ŐÉ t‚āÄ) = 0
  -- Gauge theory parallel transport: ODE on principal bundle, requires manifold ODE theory

-- ============================================================
-- Section 3: Curvature 2-Forms (Field Strength)
-- ============================================================

/-- The curvature 2-form ő© = dŌČ + ¬Ĺ[ŌČ, ŌČ] is a Lie algebra-valued 2-form
    on the total space P that measures the failure of parallel transport to commute.

    Key properties:
    1. ő©(X, Y) = 0 if X or Y is vertical
    2. R_g* ő© = Ad(g‚ĀĽ¬? ¬∑ ő©
    3. Bianchi identity: dő© + [ŌČ, ő©] = 0

    Locally, ő© = g‚ĀĽ¬?F g where F = dA + A ‚ą?A is the field strength on M. -/
structure Curvature {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (conn : Connection P) where
  /-- Lie algebra-valued 2-form on the total space. -/
  omega2 : P.totalSpace ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?‚Ą?  /-- Horizontal property: ő© vanishes on vertical vectors. -/
  horizontal : ‚ąÄ (p : P.totalSpace) (X Y : G),
    (X = 0 ‚ą?Y = 0) ‚Ü?omega2 p X Y = 0
  /-- Equivariance under right action. -/
  equivariance : ‚ąÄ (p : P.totalSpace) (g : G), omega2 (P.rightAction p g) = Ad g‚ĀĽ¬?(omega2 p)

/-- Bianchi identity: dő© + [ŌČ, ő©] = 0.

    This is the non-abelian generalization of the homogeneous Maxwell equations.
    In local coordinates: d_A F = 0 where d_A is the covariant exterior derivative. -/
postulate BianchiIdentity {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
  [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} {conn : Connection P} (curv : Curvature conn) :
  ‚ąÄ (p : P.totalSpace) (X Y Z : G),
    -- dő©(X,Y,Z) + cyclic permutations = 0
    curv.omega2 p X Y + curv.omega2 p Y Z + curv.omega2 p Z X = 0
  -- Bianchi identity: gauge-covariant exterior derivative of curvature vanishes
  -- d_A F = 0 (homogeneous Yang-Mills equation), requires differential form calculus on manifolds

/-- Field strength (local curvature 2-form) on the base manifold M.

    F_őĪ = dA_őĪ + A_őĪ ‚ą?A_őĪ (non-abelian: F = dA + ¬Ĺ[A, A]).
    Under gauge transformation: F_ő≤ = g_{őĪő≤}‚ĀĽ¬?F_őĪ g_{őĪő≤}. -/
structure FieldStrength {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] (P : PrincipalBundle M G) where
  /-- Local 2-form F_őĪ on open sets U_őĪ ‚ä?M. -/
  field : M ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?G ‚Ü?‚Ą?  /-- Local expression: F = dA + A ‚ą?A. -/
  localExpression : ‚ąÄ (x : M) (X Y : G), field x X Y = deriv (fun z => deriv (A z) X) Y x +
    ¬Ĺ * LieBracket (A x X) (A x Y)
  /-- Gauge transformation: F transforms covariantly. -/
  gaugeTransform : ‚ąÄ (x : M) (g : G), field x = Ad g‚ĀĽ¬?(field x)

-- ============================================================
-- Section 4: Yang-Mills Action and Equations of Motion
-- ============================================================

/-- Yang-Mills action: S_YM = ‚ąę_M tr(F ‚ą?*F) dvol.

    For a compact Riemannian 4-manifold M with metric g:
    S_YM = -¬Ĺ ‚ąę_M tr(F_{őľőĹ} F^{őľőĹ}) ‚ąög d‚Āīx

    This is the generalization of the Maxwell action to non-abelian gauge groups. -/
noncomputable def YangMillsAction {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] [MeasureSpace M] [RiemannianMetric M]
    {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (F : FieldStrength P) : ‚Ą?:=
  ‚ą?(x : M), -¬Ĺ * trace (F.field x) * volumeForm x

/-- The Yang-Mills equations of motion: d_A *F = 0 (source-free).

    Derived from őīS_YM/őīA = 0 via variational principle.
    This is the non-abelian generalization of the Maxwell equations:
    - d_A F = 0 (Bianchi identity) ‚Ä?automatic
    - d_A *F = 0 (equations of motion) ‚Ä?from action principle

    With sources: d_A *F = *J where J is the current 3-form. -/
postulate YangMillsEquations {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
  [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (F : FieldStrength P) :
  ‚ąÄ (x : M) (X Y Z : G), -- Covariant divergence of field strength vanishes
    -- d_A *F = 0 (source-free Yang-Mills)
    deriv (fun z => trace (F.field z)) x = 0
  -- Yang-Mills equations: variational principle őīS/őīA = 0, requires functional analysis on manifold

/-- Energy-momentum tensor for Yang-Mills fields.

    T_{őľőĹ} = tr(F_{őľőĪ} F_őĹ^őĪ) - ¬ľ g_{őľőĹ} tr(F_{őĪő≤} F^{őĪő≤}).
    Conserved: ‚ąá^őľ T_{őľőĹ} = 0 (follows from YM equations + Bianchi). -/
postulate YMEnergyMomentum {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
  [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (F : FieldStrength P) :
  ‚ąÄ (x : M), -- Divergence-free
    deriv (fun z => energyDensity F z) x = 0
  -- Energy-momentum conservation: ‚ąá^őľ T_{őľőĹ} = 0, requires covariant derivative on Riemannian manifold

-- ============================================================
-- Section 5: Instanton Solutions and Topological Charge
-- ============================================================

/-- Instanton: self-dual (or anti-self-dual) Yang-Mills connection on a 4-manifold.

    F = ¬Ī *F (self-dual: F = *F, anti-self-dual: F = -*F).
    On a compact 4-manifold, instantons minimize the Yang-Mills action
    among connections with fixed topological charge.

    The topological charge is the second Chern number:
    c‚ā?P) = (1/8ŌÄ¬≤) ‚ąę_M tr(F ‚ą?F) ‚ą?‚Ą? -/
structure Instanton {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] [RiemannianMetric M] [Oriented M]
    {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (conn : Connection P) (curv : Curvature conn) where
  /-- Self-dual or anti-self-dual condition. -/
  selfDual : ‚ąÄ (x : M) (X Y : G), curv.omega2 x X Y = HodgeStar (curv.omega2 x) X Y
  /-- Minimizes action for fixed topological charge. -/
  actionMinimizing : ‚ąÄ (conn' : Connection P), YangMillsAction (FieldStrength.mk curv) ‚Č?    YangMillsAction (FieldStrength.mk (Curvature.mk curv))

/-- Topological charge (second Chern number / instanton number).

    k = (1/8ŌÄ¬≤) ‚ąę_M tr(F ‚ą?F) = c‚ā?P) ‚ą?‚Ą?
    For SU(2) on S‚Ā? k = winding number of the transition function.
    The Atiyah-Singer index theorem relates k to the Dirac index. -/
noncomputable def TopologicalCharge {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] [RiemannianMetric M] [Oriented M] [CompactSpace M]
    {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (F : FieldStrength P) : ‚Ą?:=
  round ((1 / (8 * Real.pi^2)) * ‚ą?(x : M), trace (F.field x ‚ą?F.field x))

/-- Chern-Simons action: CS(A) = (k/4ŌÄ) ‚ąę_M tr(A ‚ą?dA + ‚Ö?A ‚ą?A ‚ą?A).

    Related to topological charge: on a closed 4-manifold,
    k = CS(A_‚ą? where ‚ąāM is the boundary (for manifolds with boundary).
    Important in condensed matter: quantum Hall effect, fractional statistics. -/
noncomputable def ChernSimonsAction {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
    [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] [RiemannianMetric M] [Oriented M] [CompactSpace M]
    {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (A : GaugePotential P) (k : ‚Ą? : ‚Ą?:=
  (k / (4 * Real.pi)) * ‚ą?(x : M), trace (A.potential x ‚ą?deriv (A.potential x) +
    ‚Ö?* (A.potential x ‚ą?A.potential x ‚ą?A.potential x))

/-- Atiyah-Singer index theorem for Dirac operator on instanton background.

    index(D_A) = dim ker D_A - dim ker D_A‚Ä?= n_+ - n_- = 8k - 3
    for SU(2) instanton of charge k on S‚Ā?
    This gives the dimension of the instanton moduli space. -/
postulate InstantonModuliDimension {M G : Type*} [TopologicalSpace M] [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G]
  [LieAlgebra ‚Ą?G] [RiemannianMetric M] [Oriented M] [CompactSpace M]
  {P : PrincipalBundle M G} (inst : Instanton conn curv) :
  -- Dimension of instanton moduli space
  dim (ModuliSpace inst) = 8 * (TopologicalCharge (FieldStrength.mk curv)) - 3
  -- Atiyah-Singer index: requires elliptic operator theory on manifolds, postulated as gauge theory axiom

